A number of metro police officers were deployed to London Road following a protest by a number of Central Johannesburg College students this morning, Alex News reports.
The students blocked the N3 and London Road with tyres.
READ MORE:Â City of uMhlathuze counting cost after Unizulu students protest
Spokesperson for metro police Wayne Minnaar said metro police were able to disperse the protesters, and both roads were cleared.


Councillor Shadrack Mkhonto said he was in communication with the students and was awaiting a list of their demands.
